0009|- [HelpText]
0010|*Footnotes can be written and placed to the end of the current page
0011|*automatically as follows:
0012|*Indicate in the text the place that refers to the footnote by the
0013|*character '*' with 'F' as the shadow character. In the final printing,
0014|*this character will be replaced by the index of the footnote.
0015|*This line must be followed an empty line and the lines containing the
0016|*footnote text. The footnote text is terminated by an empty line.
0018|*Example:
0019|S    This is text having references* to two footnotes.*
S   |                                   f                  f
0021|* This is the first footnote text.
0023|* This is the second footnote text
0024|*taking two lines.
0026|*The text continues...
0028|*The control of the page changes is automatic. PRINT takes into account
0029|*the lengths of the footnotes.
0031|*The reference numbers for footnotes are 1,2,3,... unless otherwise
0032|*stated by [footnote_number(n)] where n will be the number of the
0033|*next footnote. By using [footnote_number(1)] on header lines, counting
0034|*will be reset for each page.
0035|*The typeface etc. for footnotes is controlled by control words
0036|*[NOTE_START] and [NOTE_END]. See the proper device driver for default
0037|*settings.
